    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="408"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d408">
                <head>No. 408.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Count <persName
                            type="to">de Foresta</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 23, 1887</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Count</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    Mr. Ferrara’s note of the 27th ultimo, stating that United States vessels and
                    their cargoes are not obliged to pay any discriminating duty in the ports of
                    Italy, either as compared with Italian vessels, those of the Netherlands, or
                    those of any other country. I communicated the facts to the Treasury and have
                    received a letter from that Department informing me that Italian vessels coming
                    from the ports named in the President’s proclamation of April 22d last, of which
                    I inclose copy,<note n="*" xml:id="d408fn1">Printed <ref target="#pg_907">page
                            907</ref>, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                    </note> will be admitted in the United States under the terms of that
                    proclamation.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
